Comedy Showroom: six new comedy pilots made by some of Australia's most exciting comedians, comedy writers, producers and directors

ABC is the home of great Australian comedy and Comedy Showroom demonstrates the breadth of comedic talent in this country. Watch these six new comedy programs and share your comments.Your feedback just might shape what you watch on ABC and iview in the future. #ABCComedyShowroom

Don't miss The Daily Show's Ronny Chieng sharing his Uni experiences in Ronny Chieng: International Student; Alison Bell struggles as a new mum in an oddball mothers' group in The Letdown (produced by The Chaser's Julian Morrow); catch the desperate attempts of a deadbeat weed dealer to win his new neighbour's affections in hot WA comedy team Mad Kids' The Legend of Gavin Tanner; observe Eddie Perfect's absurd suburban life in The Future Is Expensive; The Katering Show's Kate McLennan hits rock bottom in life and love in her and Kate McCartney's Bleak and Lawrence Mooney discovers what it takes for a 40-something-year-old man to finally grow up in Moonman
